53.  THE practice of leaving great sums of money to friends, tho' one had near relations, was common in GREECE as well as ROME; as we may gather from LUCIAN.  This practice prevails much less in modern times; and BEN. JOHNSON's VOLPONE is therefore almost entirely extracted from ancient authors, and suits better the manners of those times.

